    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle and turn on your <strong>slow cooker</strong> to high</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef </strong>and<strong> bacon</strong> <strong>lardons</strong>, and cook for 5-6 min or until the beef is browned and the bacon is golden</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> in quarters</p><p>Top, tail and cut your <strong>carrot[s]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in half lengthways, then slice on the diagonal</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>red wine stock</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>stock </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Tip: Scrape any bits from the bottom of the pan as this will add extra flavour to the sauce!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> sliced mushrooms </strong>with the<strong> chopped shallots</strong>,<strong> sliced carrot </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add your <strong>finely</strong> <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>with your<strong> marmite</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix </strong>and<strong> dried bay leaf[ves]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours \u2013 this is your <strong>slow cooker</strong> <strong>beef & bacon bourguignon</strong></p><p>Once the beef & bacon bourguignon has 20 min left, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes are nearly ready, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> and the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong> with a small splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook for 2-3 in or until wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic kale</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-beef-and-bacon-bourguignon/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Discard the<strong> bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>slow cooker</strong> <strong>beef & bacon bourguignon </strong>with the <strong>mash </strong>and<strong> garlic kale </strong>to the<strong> </strong>side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
